tossup_question: -   –  In about twelve thousand years, the star Vega will be the North Star, not Polaris, due to which of the following:
tossup_MCQoptions:
W) Jupiter's gravity
X) Earth's tilted axis
Y) Earth's axial precession
Z) Earth's nutation
bonus_question: -   –  Which of the following is true of the eyewall replacement cycles of a hurricane?
bonus_MCQoptions:
W) Maximum sustained wind speeds tend to increase in the eyewall
X) A smaller eye expands outward and replaces a larger eye
Y) The core of strongest wind tends to become more compact
Z) Eyewall replacement cycles are common when a hurricane reaches a Category 5 status
bonus_answer: ANSWER: Z) EYEWALL REPLACEMENT CYCLES ARE COMMON WHEN A HURRICANE REACHES A CATEGORY 5 STATUS
